11.  2  Chronicles  13:1-12.  

2  Chronicles  13-1  בִּשְׁנַת  שְׁמוֹנֶה  עֶשְׂרֵה  לַמֶּלֶךְ  יָרָבְעָם  וַיִּמְלֹךְ  אֲבִיָּה  עַל־יְהוּדָה:
OF:מָלַךְ,  reign,  Conj-w  |  V-Qal-ConsecImperf-3ms,  he_reigned,  

T: In the eighteenth year of king Jeroboam, and Abijah reigned over Judah. 


2  Chronicles  13-2  שָׁלוֹשׁ  שָׁנִים  מָלַךְ  בִּירוּשָׁלִַם  וְשֵׁם  אִמּוֹ  מִיכָיָהוּ  בַת־אוּרִיאֵל  מִן־גִּבְעָה
OF:מָלַךְ,  reign,  V-Qal-Perf-3ms,  he_reigned,  three, years, ~, in_Jerusalem, and_name, of_his_mother, Micaiah, the_daughter_of_Uriel, from_Gibeah, 

b  וּמִלְחָמָה  הָיְתָה  בֵּין  אֲבִיָּה  וּבֵין  יָרָבְעָם:
OF:מָיָה,  it_is,  V-Qal-Perf-3fs,  she_was, and_war, ~, between, Abijah, and_between, Jeroboam, 

T: He reigned three years in Jerusalem, and the name of his mother was Micaiah, the daughter of Uriel from Gibeah. There was war between Abijah and Jeroboam. 


2  Chronicles  13-3  וַיֶּאְסֹר  אֲבִיָּה  אֶת־הַמִּלְחָמָה  בְּחַיִל  גִּבּוֹרֵי  מִלְחָמָה
OF:אָסַר,  join,  Conj-w  |  V-Qal-ConsecImperf-3ms,  and_he_joined, Abijah, -the_battle, with_army, of_valiant, of_war, 

